1:1 COMMENT "# typed_data.z -- data blocks with explicit element type via `out T`."
1:70 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# Two forms exist for declaring data blocks:"
3:45 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "#   - Untyped:  `data { ... }`            element type defaults to i64"
4:71 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "#   - Typed:    `data { ... } out T`      every element pinned to T"
5:68 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "#"
6:2 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# When the block is a constant lookup table of bytes / small ints,"
7:67 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# `out u8` keeps the C-level array narrow (one byte per slot"
8:61 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# instead of eight) without forcing per-element `.u8` suffixes."
9:64 EOL "\n"
10:1 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "# Typed: every element pinned to u8. The C emitter lays this out"
11:65 EOL "\n"
12:1 COMMENT "# as `static const uint8_t[]`."
12:31 EOL "\n"
13:1 LABEL "bytemask"
13:9 COLON ":"
13:10 WS " "
13:11 DATA "data"
13:15 WS " "
13:16 BRACEOPEN "{"
13:17 EOL "\n"
14:1 WS "    "
14:5 LABEL "LOW"
14:8 COLON ":"
14:9 WS "  "
14:11 REFID "0"
14:12 EOL "\n"
15:1 WS "    "
